LAFIA â€“ Gov. Abdullahi Sule, of Nasarawa State, has polled a total number of 698 votes to defeat Dr. Fatima Abdullahi the ex-wife of Abdullahi Adamu, the national chairman of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC), at the party primary that was conducted in the state. Mr Isa Ibeto, a returning officer in the election who declared governor Abdullahi Sule said polled 698 votes to flowed Dr. Fatima Abdullahi who scored 3 in the contest. Speaking shortly after the declaration governor Sule, said he was optimistic about the peaceful process of the exercise and promised to work closely with Dr. Fatima for APC to continue beyond 2023. -Advertisement- Also speaking shortly after the exercise Dr. Fatima Abdullahi who apart from congratulated the governor for his resounding victory said the people of Nasarawa state has decided to vote the governor back to enable him to continue with the good work he has started.